'''Nathaniel Gabor''' is a ''[[Star Wars]]'' fan who designed the [[Tibannuck]] in the [[Design An Alien]] contest held in the ''[[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine]]s''. The entry was picked 3rd place in the under 16 years old category. He was 14 at the time his entry was published.<ref name="Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 7">{{GalaxyCite|7|Design An Alien}}</ref>

Gabor was a graduate student in physics at [[Wikipedia:Cornell University|Cornell University]], and worked in their Laboratory of Atomic and Solid State Physics, researching the transport and optical properties of carbon nanotube P-N diodes.<ref name="McEuen Group">{{WebCite|url=http://www.lassp.cornell.edu/lassp_data/mceuen/homepage/people.html|text=McEuen Lab People|archivedate=20010710214719}}</ref> He is currently an associate professor at the University of California Riverside.<ref name="UCR">{{WebCite|url=http://www.physics.ucr.edu/people/faculty/gabor.html|text=Department of Physics & Astronomy: Nathaniel Gabor|archivedate=20141031151124}}</ref>

